casebody.data:
EDWIN M. WILMER vs. HENRIETTA V. LANG. Decided October 6th, 1922.

The cause was argued before Boyd, C. J., Thomas, Pattison, Urner, Stockbridge, Adkins, and Offutt, JJ.

E. M. Wilmer, for the appellant. William L. Stuckert, for the appellee. Stockbridge, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court, disr missing the appeal, with costs.
